  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CDM Project for Rural Electrification</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of the project was to set up and operate small-scale plants for the gasification of biomass such as post-harvest residues of sorghum or cotton, which in the past have simply been burned. The facilities ought to generate power from biomass by the process of pyrolysis, with annual savings of around 5,000 to 7,500 tonnes of CO2. The charcoal produced during gasification could be used as fertiliser in the fields. The project should have been developed as a Clean Development Mechanism (CDM) Gold Standard project.</narrative>
  </description>
